results.name: Array read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) is the number of k-regular loopless multigraphs on n unlabeled nodes, n >= 0, k >= 0.
comment: Terms may be computed without generating each graph by enumerating the number of graphs by degree sequence. A PARI program showing this technique for graphs with labeled vertices is given in A333351. Burnside's lemma can be used to extend this method to the unlabeled case.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..350
xref: Cf. A051031 (simple graphs), A167625 (with loops), A192517 (not necessarily regular), A328682 (connected), A333351 (labeled nodes).
results.author: _Andrew Howroyd_, Mar 15 2020
